The paper discusses a model of social interaction and segregation, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper focuses on the dynamics of online social networks and their impact on society. The second likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), as the paper uses an evolutionary game model to analyze the behavior of agents in social networks. The third likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), as the paper examines the societal dynamics of social networks. The fourth likely category is cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy), as the paper touches on the potential risks and implications of online social networks. The fifth likely category is cs.EC (Computational Economics and Finance), as the paper discusses the welfare implications of the model's predictions.
